1
00:00:57,900 --> 00:00:59,410
Call me "Daddy," Saitharn.

2
00:01:16,920 --> 00:01:21,910
♫But no one sees what's behind my smiles♫

3
00:01:22,330 --> 00:01:25,970
♫It's the loneliness I try to hide♫

4
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:31,360
♫Will there be someone my heart's seeking?♫

5
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:35,229
♫Then today, I got you near♫

6
00:01:35,259 --> 00:01:40,009
♫You made my heart drift away,♫

7
00:01:40,039 --> 00:01:41,990
♫Lost in your gaze♫

8
00:01:42,320 --> 00:01:45,470
♫Like a stream washing over me♫

9
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:50,950
♫Wanna give this a try,
like it's more than one night?♫

10
00:01:50,979 --> 00:01:54,560
♫Let's change one night into♫

11
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:56,380
♫something more, alright♫

12
00:01:56,420 --> 00:01:59,530
♫Let's follow our hearts once♫

13
00:01:59,590 --> 00:02:05,420
♫Wanna give this a try, just let me get inside?♫

14
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:11,640
♫Deep inside, I'll make you feel whole♫

15
00:02:11,880 --> 00:02:16,220
♫May I ask you to be my last?♫

16
00:02:48,150 --> 00:02:49,210
Saitharn,

17
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:51,310
shall we go again?

18
00:02:58,260 --> 00:02:59,530
I'm still not satisfied.

19
00:03:00,870 --> 00:03:02,020
Can I have you one more time?

20
00:03:04,390 --> 00:03:05,490
You fail to sate me,

21
00:03:07,030 --> 00:03:08,330
I have no need for your seconds.

22
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:10,230
If you still hunger,

23
00:03:12,020 --> 00:03:13,640
then go find someone else to satisfy it.

24
00:03:16,150 --> 00:03:17,579
How would you like it then?

25
00:03:18,210 --> 00:03:19,130
You can make a request,

26
00:03:20,710 --> 00:03:21,810
and I'll deliver.

27
00:03:22,610 --> 00:03:23,320
It'll be a good one.

28
00:03:26,620 --> 00:03:27,600
I get bored easily.

29
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:31,250
I always pivot to the next new thing.

30
00:03:33,250 --> 00:03:34,210
As for you,

31
00:03:36,350 --> 00:03:37,810
you're just as appetizing as a snack.

32
00:03:39,350 --> 00:03:40,320
So, please go home.

33
00:04:18,899 --> 00:04:21,100
[Looking for someone]

34
00:04:39,530 --> 00:04:41,420
[Chiang Rai]

35
00:04:42,700 --> 00:04:44,700
[I want to meet you. S Club, Chiang Rai]

36
00:04:45,580 --> 00:04:48,130
[I want to meet you. S Club, Chiang Rai]

37
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:56,420
[Why should I come all the way there?]

38
00:05:10,910 --> 00:05:12,870
Uncle Phon,
just follow the direction I sent you.

39
00:05:13,630 --> 00:05:15,830
Mr. Saitharn,
it is best for you not to go there.

40
00:05:17,180 --> 00:05:19,120
If I drop you off there,

41
00:05:19,470 --> 00:05:22,530
your mother will definitely
talk my ear off when I get home.

42
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:26,530
Whatever I do will upset her anyway.

43
00:05:26,980 --> 00:05:29,530
So please,
let her talk your ear off for my sake.

44
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:31,420
Oh, Mr. Saitharn!

45
00:05:32,210 --> 00:05:34,409
Tomorrow is the family reunion day.

46
00:05:34,690 --> 00:05:38,730
Your parents really wish for you to
be at home together with your family.

47
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:41,490
Moreover, you only get to
see everyone once in a blue moon.

48
00:05:42,590 --> 00:05:45,520
That's exactly why
I want to get away from them all.

49
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:48,640
I'm done pretending to smile
and listen to the older relatives' words.

50
00:05:48,730 --> 00:05:49,700
More like a family boasting day.

51
00:05:49,890 --> 00:05:52,140
"My child just graduated from
the University of Oxford.

52
00:05:52,170 --> 00:05:53,940
They have managed the company
for just a quarter,

53
00:05:53,970 --> 00:05:55,210
and revenue is already soaring
off the charts.

54
00:05:55,260 --> 00:05:56,190
What about you, Saitharn?

55
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:58,700
When will you get a job?
It's been a while since you've on a break."

56
00:05:59,290 --> 00:06:00,210
Blah, blah, blah.

57
00:06:01,330 --> 00:06:03,100
My mom just wants me to be there

58
00:06:03,130 --> 00:06:04,500
to make things less embarrassing.

59
00:06:07,180 --> 00:06:09,320
Do not think of it that way, Mr. Saitharn.

60
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:12,430
Whenever you are away from home,

61
00:06:12,510 --> 00:06:14,710
you'll always get dragged into
one incident after another.

62
00:06:15,230 --> 00:06:18,010
She is worried about you,
so she doesn't want you to go out.

63
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:20,700
[Madam]

64
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:25,000
Hello, Ma'am?

65
00:06:25,330 --> 00:06:26,810
Saitharn is in the car, isn't he?

66
00:06:27,300 --> 00:06:28,300
Yes, he is.

67
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:30,210
Hey, you rascal.

68
00:06:30,440 --> 00:06:31,810
I know that you can hear me.

69
00:06:31,930 --> 00:06:33,300
Are you not going to say anything?

70
00:06:35,260 --> 00:06:36,900
Mm. What is it?

71
00:06:37,090 --> 00:06:38,490
Where are you off to cause problems this time?

72
00:06:38,650 --> 00:06:40,230
I sent you to a business administration school

73
00:06:40,330 --> 00:06:42,540
so that we can pass on
the family business to you,

74
00:06:42,710 --> 00:06:44,850
not wasting your life away.

75
00:06:45,030 --> 00:06:47,500
Do you know what the relatives
have been saying about you?

76
00:06:47,710 --> 00:06:49,300
I'm done answering them at this rate.

77
00:06:52,890 --> 00:06:54,290
I'm sorry, then,

78
00:06:54,830 --> 00:06:57,020
for not meeting your expectations in life.

79
00:06:57,860 --> 00:06:58,820
But do you know that

80
00:06:59,300 --> 00:07:00,910
I've always been trying?

81
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:05,440
As for the relatives,

82
00:07:05,690 --> 00:07:07,710
I don't know what they'll say about me

83
00:07:08,020 --> 00:07:09,250
because I don't really care.

84
00:07:10,830 --> 00:07:13,020
But if you are going to care
about what they say that much,

85
00:07:14,550 --> 00:07:16,010
then there's nothing I can do, is there?

86
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:18,840
I care because I'm worried about you.

87
00:07:18,940 --> 00:07:20,430
I don't want them to
see you as an incompetent.

88
00:07:20,670 --> 00:07:22,470
I'm still your mother, Saitharn.

89
00:07:25,610 --> 00:07:26,720
You don't have to worry about me, Mom.

90
00:07:27,820 --> 00:07:28,630
Just know that

91
00:07:28,660 --> 00:07:31,370
if anything happens,
I'll take care of it myself.

92
00:07:31,390 --> 00:07:32,409
Easy for you to say.

93
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:33,970
When a problem arises,

94
00:07:34,110 --> 00:07:35,730
we'll see how far you can go.

95
00:07:37,730 --> 00:07:38,900
Uncle Phon, please end the call.

96
00:07:39,340 --> 00:07:40,520
Can you still hear me?

97
00:07:41,860 --> 00:07:44,130
I am afraid I have to end the call, Ma'am.

98
00:07:44,690 --> 00:07:45,590
Have a good day.

99
00:07:47,180 --> 00:07:50,620
[Phusangdao Group]

100
00:08:41,549 --> 00:08:42,010
Right.

101
00:08:46,060 --> 00:08:46,830
Hello.

102
00:08:50,740 --> 00:08:51,800
- Hello.
- Hi.

103
00:08:53,230 --> 00:08:53,830
Boss,

104
00:08:54,430 --> 00:08:56,200
we are having a meeting
this afternoon with K Group,

105
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:57,810
our business partner from South Korea,

106
00:08:58,060 --> 00:08:59,900
at S Hotel in the city.

107
00:09:00,940 --> 00:09:02,620
When it comes to exporting tea leaves,

108
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:04,890
we have to always be one step ahead.

109
00:09:08,030 --> 00:09:11,720
We received reports that Khum Rimpha
is rushing to submit their bid as well.

110
00:09:12,490 --> 00:09:14,230
We need to close the deal soon

111
00:09:15,030 --> 00:09:17,620
if we want to establish Phusangdao
as a premier brand in Asia.

112
00:09:18,870 --> 00:09:20,820
We just need to do our best.

113
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:23,000
No need to pay them attention.

114
00:09:23,460 --> 00:09:24,290
Oh...

115
00:09:25,030 --> 00:09:26,950
I'm so jealous of you.

116
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,810
You were born into a tea plantation

117
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:30,690
and grew up in the family business.

118
00:09:31,270 --> 00:09:33,000
Meanwhile, I had to start from scratch.

119
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:34,720
When I got here in my first year,
I had no idea

120
00:09:34,750 --> 00:09:36,790
how young and mature tea leaves differ.

121
00:09:36,830 --> 00:09:38,350
I was clueless.

122
00:09:39,110 --> 00:09:41,530
I, too, had to learn some new things.

123
00:09:41,730 --> 00:09:43,730
But I simply started earlier
than you, Chakkrit.

124
00:09:44,620 --> 00:09:45,690
You're as cool as always.

125
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:55,230
By the way, have Wipa and our team

126
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:57,020
prepared all of the documents?

127
00:09:57,050 --> 00:09:57,710
Yes, we have.

128
00:09:58,140 --> 00:10:00,030
Every document we need is in this bag.

129
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:02,120
We can close this deal for sure.

130
00:10:04,510 --> 00:10:07,210
Whenever we have a meeting at S Hotel,

131
00:10:07,340 --> 00:10:09,430
we also hang out at S Club afterward.

132
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:11,930
Tonight...

133
00:10:13,350 --> 00:10:15,510
I guess not only will you get
to close the deal,

134
00:10:15,980 --> 00:10:17,610
but you'll also get to

135
00:10:19,030 --> 00:10:21,750
close the deal on something else,
like the usual.

136
00:10:23,670 --> 00:10:24,760
Close the deal?

137
00:10:25,220 --> 00:10:26,400
- Yes, that's right.
- Close the deal?

138
00:10:27,390 --> 00:10:28,640
Close the deal, you say?

139
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:30,860
Say that again? I didn't quite catch it.

140
00:10:30,900 --> 00:10:32,420
- It was just a tease, Boss.
- Excuse me.

141
00:10:32,610 --> 00:10:35,600
I specifically booked
an upper-floor mountain view room.

142
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:38,770
But when I checked in, I was given
a second-floor room next to the elevator

143
00:10:38,810 --> 00:10:41,010
with a view of a metal staircase instead?!

144
00:10:41,540 --> 00:10:42,920
We are truly sorry about this.

145
00:10:43,050 --> 00:10:45,280
Let me check the availability
of a new room for you right away.

146
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:51,530
Allow me to explain.

147
00:10:51,560 --> 00:10:54,580
The room you reserved was booked
on short notice by another guest last night,

148
00:10:54,620 --> 00:10:56,060
which the system didn't update in time.

149
00:10:56,530 --> 00:10:59,460
Please accept our sincerest apologies.

150
00:10:59,970 --> 00:11:01,430
Are you sure you can
take responsibility for this?

151
00:11:01,460 --> 00:11:04,580
I paid good money for a premium room,

152
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:07,130
but the view I got is different
from what was advertised.

153
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:08,510
Then, as compensation,

154
00:11:08,540 --> 00:11:11,540
we'd like to offer you a complimentary upgrade
to one of our suites,

155
00:11:12,470 --> 00:11:16,220
along with daily breakfast tea
and a free airport transfer service.

156
00:11:18,010 --> 00:11:18,810
Are you certain?

157
00:11:19,050 --> 00:11:19,670
Yes, we are.

158
00:11:20,220 --> 00:11:22,640
We are willing to take full responsibility
and make this right for you.

159
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:31,120
Let me know once everything is ready.
I'll be waiting in the lobby.

160
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:32,610
- Thank you.
- My pleasure.

161
00:12:07,980 --> 00:12:09,510
Is everything ready for this afternoon?

162
00:12:09,570 --> 00:12:10,660
Yes, it is, Boss.

163
00:12:10,700 --> 00:12:11,280
Hello.

164
00:12:11,670 --> 00:12:12,320
Hi.

165
00:12:13,510 --> 00:12:14,640
Hello.

166
00:12:15,430 --> 00:12:16,310
Hello.

167
00:12:16,900 --> 00:12:19,640
- It's good to see you, Boss! How's everything?
- Hello, Uncle.

168
00:12:20,040 --> 00:12:20,820
Everything's going great.

169
00:12:21,170 --> 00:12:22,340
How are things? Are you tired?

170
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:24,500
If you are, don't forget to treat yourself.

171
00:12:24,530 --> 00:12:27,430
No need, I'm doing fine.

172
00:12:27,460 --> 00:12:29,870
This is nothing.

173
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:31,660
Oh, hello there.

174
00:12:31,760 --> 00:12:32,700
Hello, Boss.

175
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:35,510
Have the harvests been going well recently?

176
00:12:35,820 --> 00:12:38,010
Oh, the weather is just perfect.

177
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:41,240
The tea leaves are sprouting beautifully.

178
00:12:41,370 --> 00:12:43,800
I believe that in two to three days,

179
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:45,490
a lot of them should be
ready for harvest by then.

180
00:12:45,880 --> 00:12:49,310
This tea plot should yield around
15 or 16 kilograms, shouldn't it?

181
00:12:49,550 --> 00:12:51,400
It's 18 kilograms, to be exact, Boss.

182
00:12:52,170 --> 00:12:54,880
The tea leaves in that plot
are perfectly green and healthy.

183
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:58,330
Looks like this year is going to be
much better than the past few years.

184
00:12:58,450 --> 00:13:00,860
It's all thanks to
the drip irrigation system you set up, Boss.

185
00:13:01,290 --> 00:13:04,480
The water really reaches
the base of every single plant,

186
00:13:04,520 --> 00:13:07,370
and the tea leaves are sprouting rapidly.

187
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:10,520
At this rate, you'll need to hire
more people to pick the tea leaves.

188
00:13:11,570 --> 00:13:13,310
I've got Chakkrit working on that.

189
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:16,030
We need to harvest much more this year

190
00:13:16,350 --> 00:13:17,350
to prepare for a big deal.

191
00:13:18,220 --> 00:13:19,220
But I believe that

192
00:13:20,210 --> 00:13:21,650
we all can do this.

193
00:13:21,790 --> 00:13:22,390
You're right!

194
00:13:23,970 --> 00:13:24,710
Goodbye, Boss.

195
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:25,290
- See you.
- Goodbye.

196
00:13:25,330 --> 00:13:26,030
Thank you, bye-bye.

197
00:13:26,860 --> 00:13:28,350
Oh, Uncle.

198
00:13:28,650 --> 00:13:30,860
I heard you won big in the lottery this time?

199
00:13:30,890 --> 00:13:32,820
Just the last two digits, Boss.

200
00:13:32,950 --> 00:13:35,390
It's enough to treat
my grandchildren to Thai BBQ.

201
00:13:35,510 --> 00:13:37,200
If you get a lucky number next time,

202
00:13:37,370 --> 00:13:38,630
be sure to share it with me.

203
00:13:38,660 --> 00:13:39,720
Will do.

204
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:40,860
Oh, hello, Auntie Nong.

205
00:13:40,890 --> 00:13:41,800
Hello.

206
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:45,340
The grilled pig brain in a banana leaf
you gave me yesterday was amazing.

207
00:13:45,380 --> 00:13:46,680
I don't get to have that often.

208
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:47,630
Thank you for that.

209
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:49,610
I'm delighted to hear that you enjoy it.

210
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:52,810
I'll make some northern Thai food
for you to taste again.

211
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:54,690
I didn't just give it a taste, though.

212
00:13:54,740 --> 00:13:56,610
I stuffed myself full yesterday.

213
00:13:56,930 --> 00:13:57,930
Have to give it a thumbs up.

214
00:13:58,630 --> 00:13:59,630
- Thank you.
- Okay.

215
00:13:59,670 --> 00:14:00,570
I'll be going now, Auntie Nong.

216
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:01,230
- Alright.
- See you.

217
00:14:01,260 --> 00:14:02,020
See you.

218
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:05,650
Boss, let's take a look
at that area over there.

219
00:14:06,410 --> 00:14:07,330
We still have time

220
00:14:07,640 --> 00:14:08,930
before the meeting.

221
00:14:09,380 --> 00:14:10,020
Okay.

222
00:14:10,820 --> 00:14:11,530
I think we still have time.

223
00:14:11,570 --> 00:14:15,740
[Phusangdao Resort]

224
00:14:25,440 --> 00:14:29,790
Mok, can I even enter a pub
in the city looking like this?

225
00:14:29,880 --> 00:14:30,530
Of course.

226
00:14:30,560 --> 00:14:31,720
You look stylish and cool.

227
00:14:31,820 --> 00:14:34,340
Saeng-La, you're the sunshine of the twenties.

228
00:14:34,680 --> 00:14:36,620
Shut it, or I'll get busted!

229
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:38,280
I'm not 20 just yet.

230
00:14:38,430 --> 00:14:40,730
But I will be in the next few months.

231
00:14:40,780 --> 00:14:42,900
Tonight, let me just pretend that I am.

232
00:14:43,060 --> 00:14:44,580
Fine, kiddo.

233
00:14:46,120 --> 00:14:48,460
By the way, what do people do at a pub?

234
00:14:48,650 --> 00:14:50,280
Drinking and dancing.

235
00:14:50,580 --> 00:14:51,400
Hey, dancing?

236
00:14:51,860 --> 00:14:53,700
I know how to dance.
This one is currently trending.

237
00:15:02,320 --> 00:15:03,590
What on earth are you two doing?

238
00:15:05,470 --> 00:15:07,310
Don't you have to deliver
vegetables to the market today?

239
00:15:08,580 --> 00:15:09,580
Boss, boss...

240
00:15:10,270 --> 00:15:12,370
Can you take me and Saeng-La

241
00:15:12,410 --> 00:15:15,130
to hang out at S Club?

242
00:15:16,260 --> 00:15:18,490
We'd like to broaden our horizons.

243
00:15:18,770 --> 00:15:19,610
Please, Boss.

244
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:21,120
We beg you, Boss.

245
00:15:21,770 --> 00:15:23,190
I really want to see it for myself.

246
00:15:23,220 --> 00:15:25,080
Ever since I came out of the womb,

247
00:15:25,150 --> 00:15:26,810
I still have yet to experience it.

248
00:15:27,100 --> 00:15:28,200
Please take me there.

249
00:15:28,270 --> 00:15:29,220
Please.

250
00:15:29,420 --> 00:15:30,420
Please, Boss.

251
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:31,850
The problem is not going there,

252
00:15:32,610 --> 00:15:34,000
but it's that only Mok can enter.

253
00:15:34,750 --> 00:15:37,440
Saeng-La, I'll take you there
when you hit 20.

254
00:15:37,920 --> 00:15:39,590
See? You were too loud.

255
00:15:39,730 --> 00:15:40,900
Boss overheard us.

256
00:15:41,550 --> 00:15:44,210
He'd still know even if I didn't say it.

257
00:15:44,850 --> 00:15:45,630
What is it, Mok?

258
00:15:45,980 --> 00:15:46,620
Do you want to go?

259
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:52,220
I'll pass for now.

260
00:15:52,630 --> 00:15:54,910
I'll wait until Saeng-La turns 20.

261
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:56,850
It wouldn't be fun without him.

262
00:15:59,310 --> 00:15:59,940
Fine.

263
