477
00:38:16,370 --> 00:38:19,100
If the rooms are fully booked,
I'll sleep in a tent. That's it.

478
00:38:19,200 --> 00:38:21,230
Would you like to pay with cash
or with a card?

479
00:38:22,630 --> 00:38:24,080
- Try the card first.
- Okay.

480
00:38:24,110 --> 00:38:26,260
Paying 400 baht with a card? No problem.

481
00:38:26,380 --> 00:38:27,380
It's only 400 baht.

482
00:38:28,020 --> 00:38:30,370
This time, the card works.

483
00:38:30,610 --> 00:38:33,100
- Your transaction is complete. If you'll excuse me.
- Thank you.

484
00:38:33,130 --> 00:38:33,980
Thank you.

485
00:38:34,160 --> 00:38:34,950
Enjoy your trip.

486
00:38:35,000 --> 00:38:36,380
Right. Thank you very much.

487
00:38:36,630 --> 00:38:37,560
- Thank you.
- Alright.

488
00:38:39,220 --> 00:38:44,790
[Phusangdao Group]

489
00:38:44,810 --> 00:38:46,940
This summit holds great significance for us,

490
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:49,180
especially in terms of
preparing the location, concept,

491
00:38:49,310 --> 00:38:51,880
and the experience guests
will have at the Phusangdao farm.

492
00:38:51,940 --> 00:38:53,990
Following our recent negotiation,

493
00:38:54,030 --> 00:38:55,330
K Group, the South Korean partner,

494
00:38:55,350 --> 00:38:57,710
is likely to accept
almost all of our proposals.

495
00:38:57,760 --> 00:39:00,200
We are now down to the final stage of
officially signing the contract.

496
00:39:00,330 --> 00:39:02,510
We will use
the upcoming Northern Summit Event

497
00:39:02,540 --> 00:39:05,350
as a platform to publicly announce the deal.

498
00:39:05,490 --> 00:39:08,440
For this summit,
we will not only showcase our produce,

499
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:12,290
but we will also highlight the success of
Phusangdao Farm and the people of Chiang Rai.

500
00:39:12,420 --> 00:39:17,140
I intend for this to be the stage where
Chiang Rai tea makes its mark on the global stage.

501
00:39:17,580 --> 00:39:20,600
Currently, we have launched
three new varieties of brewed tea,

502
00:39:20,630 --> 00:39:21,960
including tea wine.

503
00:39:22,040 --> 00:39:25,240
We have successfully produced the new batch

504
00:39:25,340 --> 00:39:27,900
and completed the final fermentation trial.

505
00:39:27,930 --> 00:39:29,590
We will use our new sparkling blend

506
00:39:29,610 --> 00:39:32,750
as the new product to be
debuted at this summit.

507
00:39:32,890 --> 00:39:36,450
We have also prepared
a 3-day, 2-night package

508
00:39:36,480 --> 00:39:38,200
for our guests and tourists.

509
00:39:38,270 --> 00:39:40,310
They will get to pick tea leaves,

510
00:39:40,380 --> 00:39:41,640
try their hand at blending,

511
00:39:41,750 --> 00:39:44,550
and conclude with
a special dinner paired with tea wine.

512
00:39:45,180 --> 00:39:49,170
Following our site survey
at the Phusangdao Farm,

513
00:39:49,320 --> 00:39:51,520
we want to design the pavilion zone

514
00:39:51,560 --> 00:39:53,330
as an experience flow.

515
00:39:53,410 --> 00:39:54,900
Guests will start by entering the farm

516
00:39:54,960 --> 00:39:56,530
through the Tea Lab zone,

517
00:39:56,570 --> 00:39:59,860
then enjoy our tea wine while taking in
a 360-degree panoramic view.

518
00:40:00,020 --> 00:40:02,200
Our goal for this summit
is to turn tea drinking

519
00:40:02,310 --> 00:40:05,660
into a unique cultural experience
that inspires people to travel here.

520
00:40:05,780 --> 00:40:10,430
And we want every guest to Phusangdao Farm
to feel like they're truly a part of our farm.

521
00:40:11,010 --> 00:40:13,640
They'll get to experience
the tea-making process from start to finish.

522
00:40:14,180 --> 00:40:16,110
This is more than just a business event.

523
00:40:16,820 --> 00:40:20,280
We want to make them truly want to
experience our Phusangdao Farm firsthand.

524
00:40:21,860 --> 00:40:25,030
Therefore, we are going to expedite
closing the deal with K Group before the summit

525
00:40:25,410 --> 00:40:28,810
so we can announce there
that Phusangdao isn't just a tea farm,

526
00:40:29,100 --> 00:40:32,490
but the global leader in
the Thai tea export industry.

527
00:40:49,740 --> 00:40:50,840
- Thank you very much.
- Right.

528
00:40:50,940 --> 00:40:51,940
Thank you.

529
00:41:30,170 --> 00:41:30,930
Shit!

530
00:41:46,580 --> 00:41:48,590
Maple Syrup, are you okay?

531
00:41:49,030 --> 00:41:51,030
Hey! What kind of driving was that?

532
00:41:51,630 --> 00:41:54,550
Do you know that a single taillight
costs as much as a designer bag?

533
00:41:55,550 --> 00:41:57,120
What am I supposed to do now?

534
00:41:57,920 --> 00:41:59,540
Pay me 350,000 baht.

535
00:42:01,720 --> 00:42:02,720
What are you on about?

536
00:42:02,870 --> 00:42:05,520
Not only don't you
care if anyone is injured,

537
00:42:05,650 --> 00:42:07,260
but you're also making a scene,

538
00:42:07,300 --> 00:42:08,870
even though it's completely your fault?

539
00:42:09,130 --> 00:42:10,260
It's my fault?

540
00:42:10,300 --> 00:42:11,460
Listen! Watch your words.

541
00:42:11,830 --> 00:42:14,060
It's obvious that your car rear-ended mine.

542
00:42:14,320 --> 00:42:15,610
Are you blind or what?

543
00:42:15,980 --> 00:42:16,790
You are the one at fault.

544
00:42:16,830 --> 00:42:17,780
Take a good look.

545
00:42:17,820 --> 00:42:19,880
It's you who suddenly braked.

546
00:42:20,010 --> 00:42:20,780
What?

547
00:42:21,560 --> 00:42:23,030
Were you too busy doing your hair?

548
00:42:23,920 --> 00:42:25,060
How dare you say such things?

549
00:42:25,260 --> 00:42:26,950
Hey, how about we check the CCTV footage?

550
00:42:26,980 --> 00:42:29,180
This will prove who is at fault.

551
00:42:29,850 --> 00:42:32,510
If you'd use your brain for a bit,
how is there going to be CCTV

552
00:42:32,570 --> 00:42:34,390
in the middle of nowhere?!

553
00:42:34,700 --> 00:42:36,320
Did you get brain damage from the crash?

554
00:42:36,570 --> 00:42:37,930
Hey! Don't say that.

555
00:42:37,970 --> 00:42:39,080
I won't let you off the hook.

556
00:42:39,110 --> 00:42:40,590
Neither will I, as I'm not in the wrong.

557
00:42:40,850 --> 00:42:42,030
Keep talking. Not your fault, huh?

558
00:42:42,070 --> 00:42:43,500
You are the one at fault.

559
00:42:43,540 --> 00:42:44,250
No, you.

560
00:42:44,280 --> 00:42:46,780
Yeah, call everyone. Bring them all here.
I'm not in the wrong anyway.

561
00:42:48,380 --> 00:42:49,120
I'm not backing down.

562
00:42:49,160 --> 00:42:50,410
Neither am I. Call them.

563
00:42:50,430 --> 00:42:52,550
- Bring whoever you called here.
- What's going on here?

564
00:42:52,660 --> 00:42:53,540
Sila?

565
00:43:26,720 --> 00:43:29,940
It's a good thing that I downloaded
'Running Man Thailand' on the iQIYI app.

566
00:43:30,740 --> 00:43:33,330
I watched it during the flight,
or else I would've been bored to death.

567
00:43:34,010 --> 00:43:35,530
How did they get
one of the best actors on the show?

568
00:43:35,840 --> 00:43:37,620
That tag pulling game was so funny.

569
00:43:37,830 --> 00:43:39,180
The agent put a lot of work into this.

570
00:43:46,150 --> 00:43:48,250
Oh! Sila, you came here just in time.

571
00:43:48,280 --> 00:43:49,410
Mueanphae, is it heavy?

572
00:43:49,440 --> 00:43:50,510
Come on, let me help you.

573
00:43:51,300 --> 00:43:52,830
Thank you so much, Sila.

574
00:43:53,150 --> 00:43:56,150
I'm afraid I've been bothering you
when you picked me up on Manmuang's behalf.

575
00:43:56,190 --> 00:43:57,890
Are you tired, Sila?

576
00:43:57,920 --> 00:43:59,760
You drove all the way
from the tea farm to here.

577
00:43:59,790 --> 00:44:01,860
Not at all. I'm used to it now.

578
00:44:02,140 --> 00:44:03,450
How are you? Did you have fun

579
00:44:03,670 --> 00:44:05,600
meeting friends back in Bangkok?

580
00:44:06,080 --> 00:44:08,710
It was a blast.
I got to visit a ton of cafes.

581
00:44:08,780 --> 00:44:10,340
- Really?
- I took so many photos there.

582
00:44:10,370 --> 00:44:12,410
This uncle of a guy...
He's so ugly.

583
00:44:12,550 --> 00:44:14,890
As for you, girl,
speak with a normal tone of voice, okay?

584
00:44:15,130 --> 00:44:18,480
You're making everyone's ears
in the airport bleed.

585
00:44:24,590 --> 00:44:26,650
If you don't have the money,

586
00:44:26,680 --> 00:44:28,610
you'll have to pay for it in some other way.

587
00:44:28,780 --> 00:44:30,650
About the job you want me to do, what is it?

588
00:44:31,280 --> 00:44:33,970
From now on, get up to work at 5 A.M.

589
00:44:34,010 --> 00:44:36,470
But if you want to finish
paying your debt sooner,

590
00:44:36,500 --> 00:44:39,300
I guess you know what you have to do.
